If you get `NaN` as a result of addition, then either `table[numbers].nl` or `table[numbers].n2` must be `NaN`.

You can check whether all of these values are `NaN` by using [`Array#every`][1] and `Number.isNaN`:

```
if (Object.values(table).every(v =&gt; Number.isNaN(v.nl) || Number.isNaN(v.n2))) {
    console.log(&quot;All are NaN&quot;)
} else {
    // do the normal thing
}
```

Of course you could also just do the addition and check the  result:

```
if (Object.values(table).every(v =&gt; Number.isNaN(v.nl + v.n2))) {
    console.log(&quot;All are NaN&quot;)
}
```

