It’s rare that people want that kind of comparison, so you probably won’t find an addon that does it. But you could use a modified version of [Ember Truth Helpers’s `eq`](https://github.com/jmurphyau/ember-truth-helpers/blob/b2e3a728f4cd5b2f24cd9a5c20e99e80e72cc914/addon/helpers/equal.js) to use `==` instead of `===`:

```
import { helper } from &#39;@ember/component/helper&#39;;

export function equal(params) {
  return params[0] == params[1];
}

export default helper(equal);
```

If you place such a file at `app/helpers/double-eq` you could use it with `(double-eq 1 &#39;1&#39;)`. Probably there’s a clearer name than that, but you get the idea.

